<TEXT>
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
weighted down by the crisis in lithuania and other restive soviet 
republics is resisting proposals from president bush for a 
multisite us summit administration officials say 
the soviets have given a polite nyet to white house 
suggestions that part of the may 30june 3 summit be held at bushs 
oceanside vacation home in kennebunkport maine said officials who 
spoke on the condition of anonymity 
chances are that gorbachev who doesnt share bushs love for 
ocean power boating had his fill of waves and spray at their last 
meeting in december aboard the soviet liner maxim gorki tied up 
at malta dock in a mediterranean gale 
also not in the cards a joint bushgorbachev appearance at the 
may 31 commencement at west point bush was scheduled to give the 
keynote address and speculation grew that he might show up with 
gorbachev in tow 
administration officials said they have ruled out any such joint 
appearance and expect that bush will have to cancel his own 
participation because of the summit 
lack of soviet feedback on summit logistics is frustrating 
planning for the superpower meeting that begins seven weeks from 
today the officials said 
the upshot is that the summit probably will be held almost 
entirely in washington with a visit to the presidential retreat in 
camp david md likely to be the only side trip the sources said 
its going to be a working visit no time for sightseeing 
gennadi gerasimov the soviet foreign ministry spokesman said 
pointedly 
still bush has a record of conducting meetings with foreign 
leaders in picturesque or at least interesting places and 
taking them to sporting events 
malta is a hard locale to beat at least in photogenic terms 
but bush plans another island session this weekend when he meets 
with british prime minister margaret thatcher in bermuda 
he conferred with french president francois mitterrand last 
december on the french caribbean island of st martin and meets 
with him again later this month in key largo fla he has also had 
mitterrand to kennebunkport 
for his summit last month with japans prime minister toshiki 
kaifu bush selected a posh desert country club near palm springs 
calif 
he also likes to take foreign leaders to baseball games 
although the white house says there are no particular plans for a 
bushgorbachev outing to the ballpark 
bush joined canadian prime minister brian mulroney on tuesday 
evening for a game in the sprawling toronto skydome and a year 
ago he took egyptian president hosni mubarak to a baltimore 
orioles game mubarak had never seen a baseball game before and he 
seemed baffled 
of course with gorbachev anything is possible just like bush 
he has a history of surprise moves at summits 
for instance the last time he was in washington in december 
1987 he abruptly stopped his motorcade several blocks from the 
white house got out and greeted people on the street 
bush no doubt remembers that event all too well thenvice 
president bush was in an accompanying limousine and seemed at a 
loss to know what to do as gorbachev worked the delighted crowd 
he sat passively in his car for several minutes then as 
gorbachev was preparing to leave bush got out of his limo stood 
by it and waved to the crowd 
gorbachev also maintained his own agenda while in washington 
meeting with various interest groups and members of congress all 
without advance notice to the reagan administration 
white house officials are not ruling out such surprises at next 
months summit either from bush or from gorbachev 
however spokesman marlin fitzwater suggests that some of the 
drama has left such summits because of the frequency of ussoviet 
summits in the six years since gorbachev came to power and because 
of dramatic changes in the communist world 
i think weve long since passed the point where you can only 
meet if you have a treaty to sign he said 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
editors note tom raum covers the white house for the 
associated press 
