<TEXT>
state treasurer ann richards defeated 
attorney general jim mattox on tuesday to claim the democratic 
gubernatorial nomination after a downanddirty runoff that dwelled 
on allegations of drug use and dishonesty 
ms richards who became the first woman in texas to win either 
partys nomination since democratic gov miriam ma ferguson in 
1932 will duel with republican oilmanrancher clayton williams in 
november 
i want you to rejoice and i want you to celebrate tonight 
because this is a fantastic win ms richards told cheering 
supporters at her austin election night headquarters but she said 
democrats must unite quickly to defeat williams 
i want you to remember that there were other people in this 
primary who did not support our cause who supported someone else 
and who felt strongly that they were doing the right thing and it 
is time now that we reach out to them and tell them that we must be 
unified she said 
with 90 percent of the precincts reporting ms richards the 
1988 democratic national convention keynote speaker had 571742 
votes or 562 percent to mattoxs 445403 or 438 percent 
mattoxs loss was his first since losing a 1966 bid for 
democratic precinct chairman by three votes 
i have never made a concession speech before in my life but 
tonight i feel i must mattox said adding that he would work for 
the party in the fall 
i want to send a sincere congratulations to ann richards 
tomorrow i will be ready to help her up and down the state against 
the common enemy and the common enemy is clayton williams thats 
spelled with all dollars and no sense he said 
ms richards and mattox 46 were the top two votegetters in 
the march 13 primary 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the incumbent republican gov bill clements 72 is not seeking 
reelection 
mattoxs and ms richards meanspirited runoff race which 
included charges of drug use leveled against both candidates 
wrapped up with each decrying the way the fourweek battle unfolded 
ms richards accused mattox of profiting from public service and 
challenged him to release his income tax returns 
mattox alleged that ms richards a recovering alcoholic used 
illegal drugs including cocaine 10 years ago and challenged her 
to release medical records from her alcoholism treatment in 1980 
the last week of the campaign brought newspaper reports that 
mattox was seen smoking marijuana in the mid1970s and that ms 
richards was seen in a restroom where marijuana was allegedly being 
smoked in 1979 both dismissed the reports 
its been a very unpleasant campaign it hasnt been good for 
any of us ms richards said monday 
ms richards 56 won her first bid for public office when she 
was elected a travis county commissioner in 1976 she went on to 
win two terms as state treasurer in 1982 and 1986 
mattox won elections to the texas house in 1972 to congress in 
1976 and as state attorney general in 1982 he won reelection in 
1986 
with both candidates considered liberal democrats there werent 
many issues on which they disagreed although mattox tried to cast 
himself as the more conservative 
mattox made adoption of a state lottery his key issue saying 
the game could generate 700 million or more a year without new 
taxes 
ms richards said her campaign was for a new texas with 
improved education the economy and the environment her top 
priorities 
