<TEXT>
about 100 elementary school students protesting 
the firing of their principal clashed with stickwielding police 
tuesday and several were injured marking the second such incident 
this year school officials said 
five students aged 11 to 13 suffered bruises and cuts in the 
incident in front of the morrill elementary school on the citys 
southwest side officials at the school said 
several parents charged that officers used unnecessary force in 
breaking up the protest police spokeswoman tina vicini said no one 
was arrested and no student was seriously injured 
officers had been called to help school officials get the 
students back into the building said principal eduardo cadavid 
i guess they thought we werent going fast enough so they hit 
a whole bunch of kids said student charity kinney 
school official sharon hayes said she went outside and noticed 
an officer with a stick 
i told him i thought we could handle this without sticks 
she said he started screaming and hollering and putting his 
stick in my face he told me he knew what his job was 
teacher margaret scott said police came into her classroom and 
threatened students she did not elaborate 
my children were frightened to death she said 
for the past several weeks students have been protesting the 
local school councils refusal to renew cadavids contract 
principal firings have stirred protests at other chicago schools 
in recent months since the chicago school reform act went into 
effect at the start of the year it set up parentled locals 
councils with authority to hire and fire 
the other policestudent clash occurred last month at morgan 
park high school when several students were arrested 
