increase renewed fears of increased interest rates 
cps are unsecured promissory notes for corporations issued to 
provide shortterm financing they are sold at a discount and 
redeemed at face value and their rates are considered a key 
indicator of shortterm interest rate movement 
higher interest rates tend to discourage stock investment 
japans central bank raised its official discount rate last month 
to 525 percent from the previous 425 percent but japans central 
bank and finance ministry have since ruled out any additional 
discount rate hike 
