for 29 years there was virtually no dialogue no discussion 
we hardly knew each other we settled that in two days from a 
highly troubled situation we brought the country to a fairly 
stable situation he said 
political parties were banned in nepal in 1961 when the 
democratically elected government headed by the nepali congress 
party was sacked by birendras father mahendra ending nepals 
only experiment with westernstyle democracy 
the king has wielded power through a largely rubberstamp 
government and a national assembl dominated by his nominees 
the congress party went underground and continued to campaign 
for multiparty democracy 
a leftwing coalition joined it on feb 18 setting off a 
popular movement supported by academicians doctors engineers 
pilots and peasants 
the government last cracked down on friday when troops fired on 
200000 demonstrators as they marched on the royal palace 
witnesses said at least 200 were killed the government said 10 
people were killed and 107 injured 
for oneandahalf months a period of harshness of great 
casualties of great loss of lives has gone through this country 
we want to heal these wounds to soothe anybodys feelings wherever 
they are hurt rana said 
rana said the king by removing a reference to the ban on 
parties in the constitution has relinquished participation in 
active politics 
staterun radio continued to refer to the government as his 
majestys 
to a question on the king tolerating criticism of the monarchy 
rana said freedom of expression has been established it is 
more likely that there would be praise of the king 
under nepalese law the press or citizens are not allowed to 
criticize the institution of monarchy and the royal family 
although criticism of the government is tolerated reporters who 
have broken the law have been jailed 
birendra 44 is the heir of the shaha dynasty which has held 
the throne since the middle of the 18th century 
many nepalis especially farmers who comprise the bulk of this 
countrys 17 million people view him as the reincarnation of the 
hindu god vishnu 
