since 1983 federal courts have upheld the 19th century treaties 
that allow chippewa to hunt and fish on public property in the 
northern third of wisconsin treaty critics call the rulings unfair 
to nonchippewa hunters and fishermen complaining the spring 
spearing depletes the supply of walleye 
