april 5 
red wing minn republican eagle on americas appetite for oil 
joseph hazelwood will be doing his time cleaning up the 
oilsoaked shoreline as payment for his role in misguiding the 
exxon valdez 
the fiasco of the exxon valdez however is one tiny piece of a 
much bigger issue thats the gluttony of americans when it comes 
to cheap energy 
the overconsumption of oil places more pressure on our domestic 
sources that in turn steps up the intensity to rely solely on such 
deposits as those along alaskas north shore the tragedy of the 
exxon valdez taught us all a bitter and longlasting lesson it 
rightfully has spurred congress to pursue tougher sanctions such as 
mandatory doublehulling of ships to prevent future disasters 
in the short term the valdez incident emphasizes the need for 
the industry to hire competent employees and to operate under 
stricter standards in the long run america must reduce its 
appetite for energy if its to lessen the pressure to take the type 
of shortcuts which permitted the tragic accident in alaska 
</TEXT>
