robinson represented the states 7th district in northern 
virginia from 1970 until in 1985 when he said he was retiring 
from politics because he was frustrated wiith being in the minority 
during his tenure robinson earned a reputation as a fiscal 
conservative who pushed for a strong defense he concentrated on 
budgetary matters in the agricultural defense and intelligence 
fields 
