<TEXT>
the internal revenue service is ahead of last 
years pace in processing income tax returns 
the agency said wednesday that through april 6 it had processed 
almost 57 million returns or about 90 percent of the 663 million 
it had received at this time last year the irs had received 647 
million returns and processed 82 percent or 533 million 
almost 80 percent of the individuals and couples who have filed 
are qualifying for refunds through last week the irs had 
certified 453 million refunds totaling 386 billion compared 
with 421 million refunds worth 347 billion at this time a year 
ago 
the number of taxpayers filing by computer is almost quadruple 
the 106 million recorded during the entire tax season last year 
the irs has received 39 milion electronic returns so far this 
year it had forecast 2 million for the year 
electronic filing is available in all states this year but only 
to taxpayers who expect a refund electronic returns are filed via 
computer through irsauthorized transmissions companies which 
charge a fee for the service 
the deadline for filing a return either the electronic variety 
or the oldfashioned paper kind is midnight monday residents of 
