declined rapidly in recent weeks the swedish tt news agency quoted 
his doctor as saying 
the son of a farm worker lojohansson receied little formal 
schooling but rose to become one of swedens most prolific authors 
he became a force among the proletarian writers who based 
their stories on the lives of poor workers and peasants his 
writings in the 1930s helped end a system under which farm workers 
were strongly dependent on land owners 
lojohansson wrote some 60 works from 1927 to 1986 in 1985 
