of its operations more than a year ago said faa spokesman fred 
farrar 
he said continental responded quickly to remedy violations cited 
the deficiencies included improper weighing of an aircraft use 
of outofdate performance and planning manuals at eight airports 
operation of a boeing 727 without repairing a faulty escape slide 
and failure to repair a cargo hold heater on a dc10 within the 
required time 
other fines against continental resulting from the inspection 
and other inspections are being considered farrar said he said it 
routinely takes lawyers from several months to a year or more to 
prepare proposed fines following inspections 
several thousand cases involving possible fines against various 
airlines are pending 
under a new policy announced last month by faa administrator 
james busey airlines will be able to escape penalties if they 
quickly report and correct safety violations 
the faa has the authority to levy fines of 1000 against 
individuals and 10000 against airlines for each safety violation 
without filing charges in court 
