<TEXT>
the european space agency will sign a 10year 
agreement with the soviet union this month aimed at promoting 
cooperation for the first time in space exploration the agency 
announced wednesday 
this is a very important step forward said reimar luest 
the space agencys directorgeneral he said it would be beneficial 
to both sides 
past cooperation has been based on an exchange of letters 
between the soviet academy of sciences and the european space 
research organization one of the european space agencys 
precursors it has been concerned largely with exchange of 
scientific information 
the space activities to be covered by the new accord will 
include exploration of the solar system space astronomy and 
astrophysics earth observation and other fields working groups 
will be established to recommend joint projects the 13nation 
space agency said 
the agency said the agreement to be reassessed after 10 years 
would not call for any exchange of funds it described the accord 
as a positive development in the course of relations between the 
soviet union and western europe 
