<TEXT>
constantine mitsotakis was sworn in as 
premier wednesday ending 10 months of political deadlock to cap 
his conservative partys comeback nine years after being defeated 
by the socialists of andreas papandreou 
the new government leader immediately pledged four years of 
stable leadership his new democracy party won elections sunday 
after two inconclusive polls in june and november 
shortly after the new 38member cabinet was sworn in by greek 
orthodox archbishop seraphim at the presidential mansion the 
fledgling administration received the blessing of the nations 
elder statesman sixtime premier and former president constantine 
karamanlis 
after the 45minute meeting at karamanlis home mitsotakis said 
the 83yearold elder stateman had accepted a proposal to run for 
president karamanlis who introduced the institution of the 
presidency in 1974 relinquished his bid for reelection in 1985 
when the governing socialists reneged on a promise to back his 
candidacy 
karamanlis is almost certain to gain the 151 votes in parliament 
needed for his election 
new democracy won 150 seats in the 300member parliament in 
sundays elections on monday it gained the support of the lone 
deputy elected on the rightwing democratic renewal party ticket 
giving it a majority 
this government can and will accomplish much substantially 
and we are determined to accomplish this with a fouryear term in 
mind mitsotakis said after his cabinets first meeting 
one unusual name in the new cabinet list was composer mikis 
theodorakis who gained fame in 1963 with his score for the 
awardwinning film zorba the greek he was appointed minister 
without portfolio 
new democracy returns to power after losing to papandreous 
panhellenic socialist movement or pasok in a landslide in 1981 
during a wave of antiamericanism 
mitsotakis has promised to improve relations with the united 
states which has four military bases in greece he also has said 
he would be willing to extradite to the united states a palestinian 
suspected of involvement in the bombing of an american passenger 
jet in 1982 
previous governments were ambivalent about the bases and stalled 
on extraditing the suspect 
the new conservative government faces a 156 billion budget 
deficit and an inflation rate that reached 178 percent last month 
more than triple the european community average 
the government plans to improve the economy by slashing state 
spending streamlining the huge public sector and encouraging 
private investment 
mitsotakis has asked president christos sartzetakis to speed up 
the opening of parliament scheduled for april 23 so the 
government can present its programs and seek a vote of confidence 
next week 
after the june elections a governing new democracycommunist 
alliance indicted papandreou and senior socialists on corruption 
charges but failed to tackle pressing economic and foreign policy 
issues no trial dates have been set 
the worsening economy prompted the conservatives communists and 
socialists to join in a threeparty administration after another 
inconclusive election in november but this alliance was also 
shortlived and ineffective 
without a doubt our parliamentary majority is slim 
mitsotakis said wednesday but there is also the margin given to 
us by the broader spectrum of our people the tolerance and the 
hope that it has stored in us 
