<TEXT>
a jury wednesday began deliberating 
whether former sunday school teacher john e list was a hideous 
angel of death or was mentally disturbed when he killed his wife 
three children and mother 
lists attorney elijah l miller jr has conceded during the 
eightday trial that list 64 committed the killings 19 years ago 
but he sought a lesser verdict of seconddegree murder 
firstdegree murder as sought by the prosecution required the 
union county superior court jury to find that list acted with 
premeditation it carries a life term with parole eligibility in 
15 years seconddegree murder has a 30year maximum with parole 
possible after a third of the term 
the jurors deliberated for six hours then recessed until 
thursday morning before stopping they asked for a rereading of 
the judges instructions on the element of firstdegree murder 
willfullness deliberation and premeditation 
authorities found the bodies of lists wife helen 45 mother 
alma 84 daughter patricia 16 and sons john 15 and frederick 
13 in their 18room westfield mansion on dec 7 1971 
