unnecessary surgery 
the doctor contended the series ruined his san antonio practice 
his malpractice insurance skyrocketed and he was forced to move to 
midland where he now practices at a loss said his lawyer james 
branton 
eleven jurors one more than needed to validate the decision in 
civil court voted to award the doctor 28 million after hearing 
two weeks of evidence and deliberating six hours 
kenstv lawyer mark cannan said an appeal is likely 
adverse jury verdicts against the media are not uncommon 
cannan said but this is just round one 
branton described srivastava as a promising young surgeon who 
had performed more than 2000 openheart surgeries by the end of 
1984 he also claimed the station was out to get someone during 
a ratings period 
