<TEXT>
harold ballard the colorful and eccentric owner 
of the toronto maple leafs of the national hockey league died 
wednesday in a toronto hospital after a long illness he was 86 
ballard died of a combination of factors including diabetes 
heart problems and kidney and respiratory failure doctors at 
wellesley hospital said in a release 
ballards children harold jr william and mary elizabeth 
flynn and his longtime companion yolanda ballard had visited 
him earlier wednesday 
i was holding his hand said his oldest friend former 
toronto mayor allan lamport who had visited ballard just before he 
died he squeezed my hand it showed he understood 
his death came months after he abruptly called off a scheduled 
marriage on a caribbean island to ms ballard 57 
ballard who owned maple leafs gardens and built a fortune 
estimated at more than 100 million reveled in his reputation for 
being cantankerous and unabashedly sexist and his personality 
often made more headlines than his team 
nhl president john ziegler whom ballard once called a 
knownothing shrimp said his death marked the end of an era 
harold was his own public relations marketing and promotional 
man not only manager but performer 
in an interview in october ballard said i think that every 
girl thinks that if she hangs around with a guy that shes going to 
be his wife someday she isnt getting any headway with me 
when asked about women sportswriters in the locker room he 
said i told them once if you want to go in there you can but 
youve got to take your clothes off too 
ballard called professional hockey players overpaid and often 
criticized warmer soviet relations with the west particularly on 
the ice he once threatened to bar a soviet team from his arena for 
an exhibition match 
in 1972 ballard was convicted of fraud and theft involving 
205000 in the arenas funds and served one year of a threeyear 
sentence 
ballard spent much of the last two years in and out of hospitals 
because of diabetesrelated heart problems in july 1988 he 
underwent heart bypass surgery at toronto general hospital 
in january 1988 he had a heart attack while on vacation and 
spent almost a month in the miami heart institute in february 
1986 ballard spent 16 days in the hospital for prostate gland 
surgery 
perhaps the strangest episode in his soap opera life began in 
1982 when he met yolanda macmillan who in 1987 had her last name 
legally changed to ballard in anticipation of a wedding 
but on jan 3 just hours before the two were to be wed in the 
cayman islands ballard backed out saying he was not ready for 
marriage 
hours later ballard became ill and had been hospitalized since 
a judge in toronto declared ballard mentally incompetent and 
appointed personal and financial guardians 
william ballard referred to ms ballard as the dragon lady 
and said she had taken advantage of his fathers loneliness while 
trying to isolate him from his family 
she responded they were a longbattling family many many 
years before i came to know mr ballard it just breaks my heart to 
see this kind of discontentment 
ballard was born in toronto on july 30 1903 the only son of a 
skating company owner he began in hockey as the owner of a minor 
league team he became vice president of the maple leafs in the 
1960s and president and governor of the club in 1971 he was 
inducted into the hockey hall of fame in 1977 the year the leafs 
celebrated their 50th birthday 
he bought the hamilton tigerscats of the canadian football 
league in 1978 and sold it in 1989 
his wife dorothy died of cancer in 1968 
