<TEXT>
in the mid70s he was the youngest person ever 
selected for the new york advertising copywriters hall of fame a 
dozen years later he decided he had had enough quit his agency 
and left the business 
he asked for bids on his collection of cars and art sold the 
midtown manhattan apartment and dismissed the butler he went off 
to drive in a transcontinental automobile race he wrote a book 
about his adventures 
and now ed mccabe is back 
the former president and creative director of the scali mccabe 
sloves advertising agency that created awardwinning campaigns 
ranging from durable cars to tender chickens said tuesday he has 
joined the regional ad agency beber silverstein amp partners of miami 
mccabe 51 will become a creative partner and the agency is 
changing its name to beber silverstein mccabe amp partners 
id been in advertising for 32 years and that is a long time 
to do any one thing without a break mccabe said in an interview 
of his decision to quit the ad business in late 1986 
he had no intention of getting back into it but said in 
three years of looking around i havent found anthing else i would 
want to do 
mccabe is probably best known for creating the commercials for 
perdue chicken that used the line it takes a tough man to make a 
tender chicken the ads helped build the brand and made a 
celebrity of founder frank perdue 
he also worked awardwinning ads for volvo automobiles 
stressing their durability and safety others included hebrew 
national meats and maxell tapes 
he was a cofounder of scali mccabe sloves in 1967 and was 
elected in 1974 at the age of 35 to the new york copy clubs 
copywriters hall of fame 
fellow adman george lois calls him one of the really terrific 
copywriters of the past 25 to 30 years 
mccabe became a millionaire when scali mccabe sloves was 
acquired by the company that owned the ogilvy amp mather ad agency in 
1978 he stayed on under new ownership 
but he decided to leave both the agency and the ad business in 
late 1986 
i left because i had done enough with the company i like to 
build things but when a thing gets big it gets less new he 
said 
a few months later he competed in the grueling paristodakar 
race that runs 8000 miles through the sahara desert he dropped 
out of the competition on the eighth day of the 21day race after 
falling asleep at the wheel and running out of gas he said he and 
a partner completed the trek anyway 
the race inspired him to write a book against gravity 
which is expected to be published by warner books in june 
he wrote magazine articles did consulting work for a british ad 
agency in london and looked into starting a film production 
company discarding that idea because of the heavy costs he was 
frustrated by unsuccessful efforts to assist the losing 
presidential campaign of democrat michael dukakis 
he went back to london to finish the book in late 1988 and 
returned to the united states last summer to consider his options 
he decided against starting his own agency because i did that 
once and against returning to his old agency now a part of 
britishbased wpp group plc 
